When he told his father, Yaqub (AS) understood that this was a special `sign` from Allah — Yusuf was `destined for` greatness. But he warned him not to `share` the dream `with` his brothers.

However, Yusuf’s brothers were `jealous`. They felt their father loved Yusuf more. Their jealousy grew so strong that they planned something `terrible`. One day, they took Yusuf `far away` and threw him into a deep well. Then they returned home crying, claiming a `wolf` had eaten him.

Yusuf (AS) was alone in the dark well — but Allah was with him.

A `caravan` `passed by` and found him. He was `taken to` Egypt and sold as a slave. Though he faced `hardship`, Yusuf remained patient and faithful.

