+++</md></sn><sn><md>Years passed. The famine came — and even Yusuf’s brothers traveled to Egypt `seeking` food. They did not `recognize` him, but he recognized them.


:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-7
Instead of `revenge`, Yusuf chose `forgiveness`.

Finally, he `revealed` himself. His brothers were `ashamed` and `asked for` forgiveness. Yusuf said:

&gt; "No `blame` upon you today. May Allah forgive you."

Later, his parents and brothers came to Egypt. When they bowed respectfully `before him`, Yusuf realized that his childhood `dream had come true`.

After years of hardship, Allah raised him to honor.

